  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency health services to victims of war in Laghman Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Creating no duplication, the proposed project will address SO2 of the 2016 HRP and priorities of the health cluster which will be done by providing effective trauma care and mass casualty management to conflict affected population in 4 districts of Laghman Province. 

The project will achieve this by upgrading the capacity of Mehtarlam Provincial Hospital so that it can sufficiently provide trauma trauma services to victims of war. In addition, 3 integrated FATPs linked with CHCs will be established in Alishang, Alingar and Dawlat Shah districts of Laghman Province. 

As part of PH upgrading, additional medical and non-medical staff as well as necessary medical equipment and supplies for trauma surgeries will be provided. In additional some additional medical and non-medical staff will be hired as part of the project after the infrastructure is expanded. The project will also aim to have properly equipped male and female emergency wards, triage rooms, as well as surgical supplies. As part of this, additional rooms will also be constructed as part of infrastructure upgrading efforts.

ORCD has identified this need because of the important distance between Mehtarlam and the nearby Regional Hospitals in, Jalalabad and Kabul which are already overloaded. Therefore, it is an apparent need that the provincial hospital in the hospital becomes referral point for most of the emergency war orthopedic surgeries requiring secondary care. 

The project will be implemented in coordination with the Swedish Committee for Afghanistan (being the BPHS and EPHS implementing NGO), GCMU, Provincial Health Coordination Committee (PHCC) and Provincial Development Council (PDC), all concerned provincial departments of the government as well as the Provincial Governor and other concerned governmental authorities in the province.</narrative>
  </description>
